BROUGH AND ALL THE ROADS AROUND USED TO BE ALMOST FULL WHEN THE FAIR WAS AT BROUGH. THE LOCAL FARMERS BROUGHT ALL THEIR SPARE PONIES DOWN FROM THE FELL AND PUT THEM IN PENS AT THE SIDE OF THE ROAD TO BE SOLD AT THE FAIR.
THERE WERE LOTS OF PONIES AND CARTS. PEOPLE WOULD BE GOING INTO THE SHOPS AND HOTELS AND BUYING MANY THINGS PEOPLE WOULD BE PUSHING AND SHOVING AND THERE WOULD BE GYPSY CHILDREN PLAYING. NO ONE WOULD HARDLY BE ABLE TO MOVE.{
ON 1ST OF OCTOBER 1880 THE SCHOOL HAD 3 DAYS HOLIDAY FOR THE FAIR. IN 1908 THE HOLIDAY WAS REDUCED TO 2 DAYS. IN 1946 TO ONE DAY. IN 1964 THE HOLIDAY WAS STOPPED BECAUSE THE FAIR WAS NOT SO LARGE. APPLEBY FAIR HAD TAKEN OVER.
